N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 4626.16 - Surrender of license when revoked or suspended

State Regulations

When a license is suspended or revoked, the licensee
shall surrender such licensee's license to the municipal governing body or the
commission, whichever revoked or suspended the same, on or before the effective
date of the suspension or revocation. No license shall be valid beyond the
effective date of the suspension or revocation of such
license. Notes
